Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteRoutingHalo(25.10)                              deleteRoutingHalo(25.10)

Name
       deleteRoutingHalo  - Deletes a routing halo for a blackbox, hard macro,
       or block-level design

Syntax
        deleteRoutingHalo

       [-help]

       [-lithoHalo]

       {-allBlocks | -block <blockNameList> |  -cell  <cellNameList>  |  -inst
       <instanceName> | -designHalo}

       Deletes  a  routing halo for a blackbox, hard macro, or block-level de-
       sign. Use this command after specifying a routing halo for a  blackbox,
       hard  macro,  or block-level design. You can use the addRoutingHalocom-
       mand to add routing halos.

Parameters
       -allBlocks
              Deletes the routing halo for all blocks and black boxes.

              Data_type: bool, required

       -block <blockNameList>
              Deletes the routing halo for the specified blocks.

              Data_type: list, required

       -cell <cellNameList>
              Deletes the routing halo for the specified cells.

              Data_type: list, required

       -designHalo
              Deletes the routing halo at the design level.

              Data_type: bool, required

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each deleteRoutingHalo parameter. For a detailed
              description  of  the  command and all of its parameters, use the
              man command:

              man deleteRoutingHalo

       -inst <instanceName>
              Specifies that the routing halo should be added to the specified
              instance. Use this option to delete the halo of an I/O  pad  in-
              stance.

              Data_type: list, required

       -lithoHalo
              Deletes the litho routing halo.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The  following  command delete the routing halo for all blocks
                and black boxes .

                deleteRoutingHalo -allBlocks

